        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> 100Kb in filesize would only be a problem for people that are trying something wierd, like long animated gifs or pure bitmaps and so on.<BR>100Kb should maybe more be a guideline for the max. filesize.</P><P>As for width and height.<BR>I assume most users are using 800x600 or higher.<BR>From the height of 600, some is used for toolbars, statusbars and so on in most browers. A large value on the guessed area used would be 200 pixels of 600 available.<BR>From the width of 800, some is used for window frames, margins and poster information, taking away around 200 pixels too here.</P><P>What is left is 600x400 for the messages.<BR>A width of 400 is not really a problem, since the messages do not expand in the width.<BR>A height of 600 would take all the space from the text, so a limit here would be nice. Maybe half the max. of the available size, which would be 300.</P><P>I am on a 4Mb/s leased line, so bandwidth is no problem at my end, but I get routed through level3.net, when I hit New York from Europe and level3.net pretty often got a bandwidth problem that makes the boards slow.<BR>Now just because its slow for me does not mean you have to put up very restrictive limits.<BR>I just mentioned the problems, because some might also have the problems or other problems that makes the site load slowly.</P><P>I think setting some kind of limits, even if they might not touch 99,9% of the users, will be a good idea, so the users that sometimes go mad in the things they are making got a guideline to stick too.</P><P><BR> </font></td>
